===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|かみ}}
{{wp|ja:}}
{{wp|Kami}}
{{wp|God}}

{{IPAfont|⟨kami<sub>2</sub>⟩}} → *{{IPAchar|/kamɨ/}} → {{IPAchar|/kami/}}

From {{inh-lite|ja|ojp|-|sort=かみ}}, ultimately from {{inh-lite|ja|jpx-pro|sc=Latn|*kamui|sort=かみ}}.

Not related to {{m-lite|ja|sc=Jpan|上||tr=kami<sub>1</sub> → kami|[[top]], [[upper]]}} or {{m-lite|ja|sc=Jpan|髪||tr=kami|[[hair]]}}.

Often appears in compounds as ''kamu-'' or ''kan-'', indicating that ''kami'' is an unbound form deriving from *{{IPAchar|/kamui/}}. Such apophony has occurred in other {{cog-lite|ja|-}} terms, such as {{m-lite|ja|sc=Jpan|目||tr=me, ma-|[[eye]]}} or {{m-lite|ja|sc=Jpan|酒||tr=sake, saka-|[[sake]], [[liquor]]}}. See also [[WT:AJPX#Standalone forms and combining forms]].

Compare {{cog-lite|ko|sc=Kore|검|tr=geom|t=[[god]], [[spirit]]}} and {{cog-lite|ain|sc=Kana|カムイ|tr=kamuy|t=god}}.

